Warrant from Michigan Attachment for Criminal Complaint

9:33 AM Prosecuting attorney Jedidiah J Dodge in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Jonathan Earl Cox not in court.  Attorney Maxwell Bergner in court for Jonathan Earl Cox. 
Court calls the case.
Matter set for an extradition hearing.
ADA Dodge states appearances and notes the defendant's non-appearance.
Atty Bergner does not know the whereabouts of the defendant.
ADA Dodge requests a warrant be issued for the defendant and that any cash bond be forfeited.
Atty Bergner has no position.

BY THE COURT:
Warrant authorized. Body only.
Cash bond forfeited.
Extension of 30 days to obtain a governors warrant is granted.
Extradition hearing on June 1, 2022 at 09:30 am.

8:32 AM Prosecuting attorney Jedidiah J Dodge in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Jonathan Earl Cox in court.  Attorney Maxwell Bergner in court for Jonathan Earl Cox. 

Atty Dodge makes statements to the court.  The state would like time to confirm the individual in custody is the correct defendant based on statements made by the defendant. 
Atty Bergner makes statements to the court.  The defendant is contesting the extradition and would like a hearing. 

Atty Dodge request a $500 cash bond. 
Atty Bergner makes bond arguments. 
Court questions the defendant. 
Defendant responds. 

Counsel are to meet with the Branch 2 Judicial Assistant to schedule the extradition hearing.

1:35 PM Defendant Jonathan Earl Cox in court. Prosecuting Assistant District Attorney (ADA) Kelly A Cassidy in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Court Commissioner informs the parties that this matter needs to be heard in front of a Judge.
Atty Soule informs the court that the Defendant is the wrong Jonathan Cox who has an identical conjoined brother separated at birth.
Defendant states they would have the same Identical name, DNA, and fingerprints.
ADA Cassidy informs the court that they have been researching this statement however still requesting that the defendant remain in custody until they verify.
Extradition hearing scheduled for May 13, 2022 at 08:30 am.
